name: Pearl Continental Lahore
description: Luxury 5-star hotel in Mall Road with world-class amenities including outdoor pool spa fitness center and multiple dining options. Perfect for business and leisure travelers

name: Avari Hotel Lahore
description: Modern business hotel located in central Lahore offering comfortable rooms meeting facilities gym and executive lounge. Ideal for corporate travelers and families

name: Marriott Hotel Lahore
description: International 5-star hotel chain with premium amenities rooftop pool fine dining restaurants spa and extensive banquet facilities. Located near commercial district

name: Faletti's Hotel Lahore
description: Historic heritage hotel dating back to 1880s offering colonial charm modern comfort excellent location near Mall Road and Lahore Museum. Budget-friendly luxury

name: Best Western Lahore
description: Comfortable mid-range hotel with modern rooms complimentary breakfast free wifi business center and airport shuttle. Great value for money

name: Hotel One Gulberg
description: Budget-friendly hotel in upscale Gulberg area offering clean rooms basic amenities 24-hour service and proximity to shopping malls and restaurants

name: Luxus Grand Hotel
description: Boutique luxury hotel featuring contemporary design suites with city views rooftop restaurant infinity pool and personalized concierge services

name: Hospitality Inn Lahore
description: Family-friendly hotel near Jilani Park offering spacious rooms kids play area swimming pool and traditional Pakistani cuisine restaurant

name: Badshahi Mosque
description: Historic 17th century Mughal mosque built by Emperor Aurangzeb. One of the largest mosques in the world with stunning red sandstone architecture. UNESCO World Heritage nominee

name: Shalimar Gardens
description: UNESCO World Heritage Mughal garden complex built in 1641 featuring three terraced levels fountains pavilions and beautiful landscaping. Perfect for peaceful walks

name: Lahore Fort
description: Massive Mughal era fortress complex containing palaces museums halls of audience and the famous Sheesh Mahal (Palace of Mirrors). UNESCO World Heritage Site

name: Food Street Gawalmandi
description: Famous traditional food street offering authentic Lahori cuisine including nihari karahi kebabs and traditional sweets. Vibrant atmosphere especially at night

name: Packages Mall
description: Modern shopping and entertainment complex featuring international brands cinema multiplex food court kids play area and ample parking

name: Lahore Museum
description: Largest and oldest museum in Pakistan showcasing Gandhara art Mughal artifacts ancient manuscripts and the famous Fasting Buddha statue. Rich cultural heritage

name: Minar-e-Pakistan
description: National monument commemorating Pakistan independence built at site of 1940 Lahore Resolution. 70-meter tower with observation deck offering panoramic city views

name: Emporium Mall
description: Mega shopping destination with luxury brands entertainment zone rooftop dining restaurants cinema and indoor theme park. Family entertainment hub

name: Wazir Khan Mosque
description: Stunning 17th century mosque famous for intricate tile work calligraphy and frescoes. Located in Walled City showcasing finest Mughal architecture

name: Jilani Park (Race Course Park)
description: Large urban park with boating lake jogging tracks children playground sports facilities and green spaces. Perfect for family picnics and outdoor activities

name: Lahore Zoo
description: Historic zoo established 1872 housing diverse wildlife including Bengal tigers African lions elephants and exotic birds. Educational and family-friendly

name: Cuckoo's Den Restaurant
description: Rooftop restaurant in old Haveli overlooking Badshahi Mosque serving traditional Pakistani cuisine in historic ambiance. Popular for cultural experience

name: Liberty Market
description: Popular shopping district offering clothing jewelry electronics street food and local handicrafts. Bustling atmosphere with traditional bazaar experience

name: Anarkali Bazaar
description: Historic bazaar dating back Mughal era offering traditional clothing jewelry handicrafts fabrics and street food. Authentic shopping experience

name: Lotus Lake Park
description: Scenic lake park with walking trails paddle boats picnic spots and lotus flowers. Peaceful retreat from city hustle ideal for evening strolls
